  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective observational registry of clinical pump performance data collected across three cardiac surgery centres, which the assessment narrative characterises as providing controlled, experiment-like conditions owing to the standardised data-collection protocol and pre-specified outcome definitions. The registry data are cited extensively in the output-comparison and test-conditions rationale and are treated throughout as functionally equivalent to controlled experimental data.",
